03/01/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria will send up to 30 more troops to the NATO-led forces in Afghanistan early next year, the cabinet decided at its last session for 2009 on Wednesday (December 30th).
Thus, the number of Bulgarian troops in charge of security at the Kandahar airport zone will reach 300, while the total number of Bulgarian troops in the mission will reach 497.
(Mediapool - 31/12/09;
AP, Trud, bTV, Evropa TV, - 30/12/09)
